Package: scimesh
Type: Package
Title: Headless 3D Mesh Rendering Engine
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Tim", "Schaefer", email = "ts+code@rcmd.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Author: Tim Schaefer
Maintainer: Tim Schaefer <ts+code@rcmd.org>
Description: A minimal, fast, headless 3D software renderer written in modern
    C++ with native R bindings. Serves as a zero-dependency, fallback rendering
    engine for 3D meshes when traditional GPU-backed frameworks are unavailable.
    Produces in-memory RGBA images or PNGs suitable for scientific mesh
    visualization, e.g., in neuroimaging applications. Supports basic lighting,
    shading, and camera controls.
